## Goal
Add integration tests for the full rust-bucket workflow.

## Tasks
1. Create `tests/integration.rs`:

2. Test init flow:
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_init_on_fresh_repo() {
       // Create temp dir with Cargo.toml and .git
       // Run apply_init
       // Assert all managed files created
       // Assert rust-bucket.toml created
   }
   ```

3. Test conflict detection:
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_init_fails_on_conflict() {
       // Create temp dir with existing AGENTS.md
       // Run apply_init without force
       // Assert error with conflict list
   }

   #[test]
   fn test_init_force_overwrites() {
       // Create temp dir with existing AGENTS.md
       // Run apply_init with force=true
       // Assert AGENTS.md was overwritten
   }
   ```

4. Test update flow:
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_update_preserves_config() {
       // Create temp dir with rust-bucket.toml (custom timeout)
       // Run apply_update
       // Assert timeout preserved in regenerated files
   }
   ```

5. Test version stamping:
   ```rust
   #[test]
   fn test_version_stamp_in_generated_files() {
       // Run apply_init
       // Check each generated file has version comment
   }
   ```

## Success Criteria
- `cargo nextest run` passes
- All test cases cover happy path and error paths
- Tests complete within 120s timeout

